French lentils

Ingredients
1 cup French (green) lentils
1 onion 
2 large carrots
1 tablespoon red wine vinegar
A bunch of parsley 
3 tablespoons olive oil
2 cups of water
Salt and pepper

Instructions
Combined the lentils with 2 cups of water in a pot. 
Bring pot to a boil, then reduce to a gentle simmer. 
Cook for 20-25 minutes, uncovered. Add water to keep lentils covered as necessary. 
Once lentils have softened, remove from heat and strain lentils. Reserve some of the strained water in case lentils dry.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and some ground pepper to the lentils. Stir and let cool.
Add 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar and 3 tablespoons olive oil to the lentils.

In a pan, chop and sautee the onion and carrots in olive oil.
Once the carrots and onions have softened, remove from heat.

Finely chop the parsley. 

Combine the onions, carrots, and parsley with the lentils. Add salt and olive oil to taste. Eat or keep in the refrigerator.
